OL,3,CWhere are all the April showers and
OL,4,Cwhy is the 'omega block' to blame?
OL,6,FAn omega high over Scandinavia meant
OL,7,Fthat rain-bearing low-pressure systems
OL,8,Fstalled on either side, resulting in
OL,9,Fweeks of hot, dry weather.
OL,11,FThis brought record-breaking
OL,12,Ftemperatures in countries like Sweden
OL,13,Fand Finland, and severe drought and
OL,14,Fwildfires in Scandinavia.
OL,16,FA persistent omega high helped trap
OL,17,Fvery hot air over western Europe,
OL,18,Fwhich caused the UK to record its
OL,19,Ffirst-ever temperature above 40C.
OL,26,@{D@`OX
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
