OL,3,CWhere are all the April showers and
OL,4,Cwhy is the 'omega block' to blame?
OL,6,FCertainly for the rest of the working
OL,7,Fweek before low pressure finally
OL,8,Fstarts to edge in from the southwest,
OL,9,Fbreaking the blocking pattern.
OL,11,FBefore that, though, the centre of the
OL,12,Fhigh pressure shifts a little and
OL,13,Fsoutherly winds start to draw in a
OL,14,Ffeed of very warm air from Europe.
OL,16,FThis is likely to result in
OL,17,Ftemperatures rising to around 26C by
OL,18,Fthe end of the week, before the
OL,19,Finevitable arrival of thunderstorms
OL,20,Facross many southern areas on Saturday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
